-- Lloyds Said to Set Covered Bond Size at 1.25 Billion Pounds
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-01-20T10:59:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/lloyds-said-to-set-covered-bond-size-at-1-25-billion-pounds.html
Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  set the
size of its sale of covered bonds maturing in 2025 at 1.25
billion pounds, according to a banker involved in the
transaction.  The bonds will be priced to yield 270 basis points more
than gilts, the banker said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
